  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why does my girlfriend of 7 years dont reply to my text or calls when she says that it wont be long. what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're going through this\u2014it can be really frustrating and confusing when someone you care about doesn't communicate as expected. Here are some steps you can take to address the situation:\n\n### 1. **Give Her Space (Temporarily)**\n   - If she\u2019s indicated that she\u2019ll be back soon, she might be dealing with something personal or just needs some space. Respect that and avoid bombarding her with messages or calls, as it could push her further away.\n\n### 2. **Reflect on the Situation**\n   - Think about any recent events or conversations that might have led to this behavior. Has there been tension, misunderstandings, or changes in your relationship dynamics?\n\n### 3. **Communicate Clearly When She Responds**\n   - When she does reach out, express your feelings calmly and without blame. For example, \u201cI\u2019ve been worried because I didn\u2019t hear from you. Is everything okay?\u201d This opens the door for honest communication.\n\n### 4. **Set Boundaries and Expectations**\n   - If this behavior is recurring, have a conversation about how it affects you. Let her know that consistent communication is important to you and discuss ways to improve it together.\n\n### 5. **Consider Her Perspective**\n   - She might be dealing with stress, work, family issues, or even something related to your relationship. Try to approach the situation with empathy rather than frustration.\n\n### 6. **Evaluate the Relationship**\n   - If this pattern continues and she\u2019s unwilling to address it, it might be worth reflecting on whether your needs are being met in the relationship. Healthy relationships thrive on mutual respect and communication.\n\n### 7. **Take Care of Yourself**\n   - While you\u2019re waiting for her response, focus on your own well-being. Spend time with friends, pursue hobbies, or do something that helps you relax and stay positive.\n\nIf this behavior is out of character for her, it\u2019s possible she\u2019s going through something temporary. However, if it\u2019s a recurring issue and she\u2019s unwilling to communicate or work on it, it may be a sign of deeper problems in the relationship. Ultimately, you deserve someone who values and respects your time and feelings.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
